<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Timing Gear Train and Front
        Cover - Install - Install Air Compressor and Power Steering Pump (If Equipped)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s210010805.4" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="6">
        <title>Install Air Compressor and Power Steering Pump (If Equipped)</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>When installing air compressor, it is critical that all bolts are tightened in same sequence as
                    described in Steps 2 through 5 to avoid warping front cover.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a small amount of assembly grease to O-ring and install in groove on front cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mount air compressor on front cover with mounting bolts. Tighten mounting bolts to "
                <hotlnk document="eges2101_230.xml" xrefid="t210010802">Special Torque</hotlnk>
                ."
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid engine damage, do not overtighten air compressor mounting bolts or front cover may
                        warp or fracture.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010834" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5066.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Install air compressor</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place air compressor bracket against crankcase. Slide bracket forward to air compressor
                mounting face. Install two bolts finger tight to hold bracket to crankcase.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010835" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5063.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Install air compressor rear bracket</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fasten air compressor bracket to air compressor with two bolts and two washers. Tighten
                bolts to "
                <hotlnk document="eges2101_230.xml" xrefid="t210010802">Special Torque</hotlnk>
                ."
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010836" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5062.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Air compressor rear bracket mounting bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten two air compressor bracket mounting bolts to crankcase to "
                <hotlnk document="eges2101_230.xml" xrefid="t210010802">Special Torque</hotlnk>
                ."
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010837" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5061.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Rear air compressor bracket mounting bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two coolant hoses on air compressor and crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010838" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg6/EG6170.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Install coolant hoses</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil lubrication line on air compressor and tighten nuts on both ends of lubrication
                line.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010839" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg6/EG6171.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Install oil lubrication line</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mount steering pump to air compressor and tighten both bolts.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
